This paper deals with Bayesian Neural Networks, which are commonly used in machine learning and fall under the category of deep learning. The paper also discusses the issue of non-identifiability, which is a common problem in statistical modeling. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as these sub-categories are closely related to deep learning. The paper also discusses the use of latent variables, which are commonly used in neural networks and can be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the use of uncertainty estimates, which is a common topic in statistics and can be categorized under cs.ST (Statistics).
